.TH REBOOT 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
reboot \- reboot the system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B reboot
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B reboot
is a thin convenience wrapper around
.BR "sudo systemctl reboot" .
It takes no arguments and prompts for a sudo password if the user's
cached sudo credentials have expired.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Reboot the system:
.B reboot
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
Reflects the exit status of
.BR "sudo systemctl reboot" .
On success the system reboots and this command does not return.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR shutdown (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
